# Institution-Grade AI Investing Engine

Modular quant + AI hybrid investing system prototype built around strict point-in-time controls.

## What This Prototype Covers

- Point-in-time market and news ingestion with mandatory `TimeGate(as_of_date)` filtering
- Feature engineering and offline/online feature persistence
- Parallel intelligence layer for market, text, and tabular signals
- Regime detection and regime-aware signal fusion
- Uncertainty estimation from model disagreement and data quality
- Risk-adjusted RL-style decision layer with explicit transaction-cost deduction
- Execution layer with commission, spread, and impact modeling
- Feedback capture for realized outcomes
- JSON-compatible end-to-end output for downstream systems

## Package Layout

```text
investing_engine/
  data/          # point-in-time ingestion and event publishing
  features/      # offline and online feature storage
  intelligence/  # parallel alpha models
  fusion/        # regime detection and signal fusion
  uncertainty/   # confidence and dispersion modeling
  rl/            # reward and decision engine
  execution/     # cost model and order generation
  feedback/      # realized outcome capture
  pipeline/      # orchestration
```

## Quick Start

```bash
python -m venv .venv
.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
pip install -r requirements.txt
python -m investing_engine.cli --pretty
```

## Environment

Copy `.env.example` to `.env` and adjust the values if you want to use live services.

## Testing

```bash
pytest
```

## Design Notes

- Every market and news read is gated by `TimeGate`.
- Transaction costs are estimated before order generation and included in the decision context.
- The provided prompt excerpt did not include the final RL reward equation, so the prototype isolates reward weights in `investing_engine/config.py` for easy replacement.
- The enforced prototype build sequence lives in `configs/build_sequence.yaml`, with validation helpers in `src/project/build_sequence.py`.
